==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thallogen
<hw>Thal"lo*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ young
shoot or branch, frond + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>One of a large class or division of the vegetable kingdom, which
includes those flowerless plants, such as fungi, algae, and lichens,
that consist of a thallus only, composed of cellular tissue, or of a
congeries of cells, or even of separate cells, and never show a
distinction into root, stem, and leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thalloid</ent>⟦br⟧
